               <p>The Petticoat was produced in court and deposed to by Judson.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t17750426-99-person819">
                  Thomas
                   Grime
               <interp inst="t17750426-99-person819" type="surname" value="Grime"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17750426-99-person819" type="given" value="Thomas"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17750426-99-person819" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I was at my father's, opposite Wallfords, I saw the prisoner take the petticoat from a hook at the door post, I informed Mr. Judson of it, we pursued him and took him; it was between eleven and twelve at noon, he was not out of sight before he was taken, I saw him drop the petticoat.</p>
               <p>The Prisoner said nothing in his Defence.</p>
